1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about language models and their performance. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the scaling of model size and dataset size, which are important topics in machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with neural language models, which are a type of AI model. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the architecture and training of neural models. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with computer vision, but it does discuss the effects of network width and depth on language model performance, which are also important in computer vision models.
